author: NEW YORK DAILY NEWS
title: Gunman who killed man in Bronx strip club fight identified
text:
NYPD Police are looking for Garett Warren, 26, who allegedly gunned down a man outside a Bronx strip club. A gunman who fatally blasted a man after he intervened in a fight between two strippers outside a Bronx jiggle joint has been identified, police said Sunday.
Garett Warren, 26, of Decatur Ave. in the Bronx killed Jose Feliciano, 45, as he was leaving the Key Club Cabaret on Boston Rd. in Eastchester early on Oct. 9, police said.
According to police sources, Feliciano, a regular at the club, saw the two women fighting and started defending one. Warren, who is believed to be the other womanâ€™s boyfriend, stepped in and started arguing with Feliciano.
When the words turned to blows, the boyfriend pulled out a gun and opened fire, hitting Feliciano in the stomach, according to authorities and sources. He then followed the wounded man as Feliciano tried to hide behind a car and blasted him in the head.
Feliciano died at Montefiore Medical Center.
Cops ask anyone with information on the 6-foot-3, 200-pound Warren to call Crime Stoppers at (800) 577 TIPS. All calls are confidential.
jstepansky@nydailynews.com
